"With the support of the UK government, donors, national governments and global citizens like you, we can make the social injustice of malnutrition a mere historical note," said Power of Nutrition Ambassador Tracy Ullman to the audience at a live concert in London in April 2018.
The group also said that after more than 5,000 actions were taken calling on the UK to improve maternal and child nutrition, the government had reported funding for a project, "The Power of Nutrition", that would reach 5 million women and children.
In response to one of the FAQs on his website asking "Why do you think we can end extreme poverty?"
"Global Citizen" replied: This will be a long and difficult road - sometimes we will fail and still fail.
But just as with the big civil rights movement and anti-apartheid movement before us, we will succeed because we are stronger together.
